h that GJ 1214 is a single-planet\nsystem within these limits, a result that has a $44^{+9}_{-5}$% probability\ngiven the prevalence of multi-planet systems around mid-M dwarfs. We also\ninvestigate mid-M dwarf RV systems and show that the probability that all\nreported RV planet candidates are real planets is $<12$% at 99% confidence,\nalthough this statistical argument is unable to identify the probable false\npositives.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Jul 2021 16:12:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-13"}
